<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="call-v">call <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /kɔːl/    美 /kɔːl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>召唤；大声喊 / 叫：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Will you call the kids in for lunch? 
把孩子们叫进来吃午饭好吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Listen! Do you hear someone <strong>calling (out) for</strong> help?
听！你听到有人在（大声）呼救吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="2-name">2.★ <strong>命名；把...叫做(name)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They’ve decided to call the baby Anna. 
他们决定给宝宝取名为安娜。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>认为……是：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I wouldn't call Chinese an easy language.
我不认为中文是一门容易学的语言。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>召开；召集：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>call a meeting 
召开会议</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>(给...) 打电话：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>For further information please call 0161 245 6609.
欲知详情，请致电01612456609。</p><footer>2011 陕西</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please call again later. 
请稍后再打电话。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="call-at">call at</h3>
<p>1.<strong>拜访（某地）；（火车等）短暂停留</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="call-back">call back</h3>
<p>1.<strong>回电话；再打电话：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She wants you to call her back as soon as you are home.
她要你一到家就给她回电话。</p><footer>2009 全国</footer></div>

<h3 id="call-for">call for</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>需要；要求：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sometimes situations call for us to act strong and brave.
有时形势要求我们表现得强大、勇敢。</p><footer>2011 广东</footer></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>去 (某处) 接人 / 物：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ll call for you at your home. 
我会到你家接你。</p></div>

<h3 id="call-in">call in</h3>
<p>1.<strong>召来；找来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Your mother is very ill. Call in a doctor at once. 
你妈妈病得很严重，马上找个医生来。</p></div>

<h3 id="call-it-a-day">call it a day</h3>
<p>1.<strong>［非正式用语］结束；到此为止：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let’s call it a day and go and have a bite.
咱们到此为止，去吃点东西吧。</p><footer>2009 浙江</footer></div>

<h3 id="call-off">call off</h3>
<p>1.<strong>取消 (cancel)；停止进行：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>call off a meeting / one’s appointments 
取消会议/约会</p></div>

<h3 id="call-on-upon">call on / upon</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>拜访 (某人)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ll take a walk and then call on some friends.
我要去散步，然后拜访一些朋友。</p></div>

<p>2.<strong>号召；要求：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The Ministry of Education calls on students to exercise for an hour every day. 
教育部要求学生每天锻炼一个小时。</p></div>

<h3 id="call-up">call up</h3>
<p>1.<strong>打电话给；使人想起：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ll call you up when I need your help. 
我需要你帮助的时候会给你打电话。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This picture called up memories of our class trip. 
这张照片使我想起我们班的那次旅行。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Developing the Yangtze River Economic Belt is a systematic project which calls <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ a clear road map and timetable.  （2018 江苏改）  </li>
<li>— Dr. Jackson is not in his office at the moment.
— All right. I <strong><em>_</em></strong> (call) him later.  （2015 北京改）  </li>
<li>The Somali robbers’ frequent attacks on the sea urged the United Nations to call <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ all nations to take immediate action.  （2009 福建改）  </li>
<li>As I grew up in a small town at the foot of a mountain, the visit to the village called <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ scenes of my childhood.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. for  2. will call  3. on / upon  4. up  </p></div>